# NSPersistentStoreUbiquitousTransitionType.initialImportCompleted

**Case**

This value indicates that the Core Data integration has finished building a store file that is consistent with the contents of the iCloud account, and is ready to replace the fallback store with that file.

## Declaration

```swift
case initialImportCompleted
```

## Constants

- **NSPersistentStoreUbiquitousTransitionType.accountAdded**: This value indicates that a new iCloud account is available, and the persistent store in use will or did transition to the new account.
- **NSPersistentStoreUbiquitousTransitionType.accountRemoved**: This value indicates that no iCloud account is available, and the persistent store in use will or did transition to the “local” store.
- **NSPersistentStoreUbiquitousTransitionType.contentRemoved**: This value indicates that the user has wiped the contents of the iCloud account, usually using Delete All from Documents & Data in Settings.
